# Creator Collective Domain

**Owns:** creator/brand profiles, campaigns, reverse bids/proposals, messaging, deliverables, campaign payments, ratings.  
**Does not own:** gift engraving, medical article review, Soft Gift cart.

## Honest repo state

`CreatorModule` is still **empty scaffolds** (`campaigns`, `proposals`, `deliverables`, …). When you implement, follow invariants below — don’t invent LMS or Gift Commerce shortcuts. Roles already seeded: `CREATOR`, `BRAND`.

## Invariants (enforce as soon as endpoints exist)

| Invariant | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Closed / awarded campaign | Reject new proposals |
| Award | Explicit rules; **single-winner default** unless PRD says multi |
| Escrow / campaign pay | Release only after deliverable approval gate |
| Ownership | Brand sees own campaigns; creator sees own proposals — IDOR-safe |
| Ratings | Only after eligible completion states |

## State machines (target)

Campaign: `draft → open → reviewing → awarded → in_delivery → completed | cancelled`  
Deliverable: `submitted → changes_requested → approved`  
Illegal jump → `409` + stable code. Money paths: `*Paise` Int + idempotent payout keys (same bar as commerce/editorial).

## UI

Always `data-theme="creator"` (Playfair + Manrope, forest/terracotta from `globals.css`).  

```text
❌ Soft Gift pink / Fraunces on creator trees
❌ Treat SpecialistProfile (editorial) as a marketplace creator
```

Cross-domain: no Prisma into `commerce_*` / `articles` tables from creator modules — use events or ACL ports.
